dot4Table.name: dot4Table
dot4Table.description: This table contains Token Bus interface parameters and state variables, one entry per 802.5 interface.

dot4Entry.name: dot4Entry
dot4Entry.description: A list of Token Bus status and operational parameter values for an 802.4 interface.

dot4IfIndex.name: dot4IfIndex
dot4IfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the 802.4 interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex object, defined in [4,6], for the same interface.

dot4Options.name: dot4Options
dot4Options.description: The optional parts of the 802.4 specification which are in use by this station. The options of the 802.4 specification are represented by the following values: 1 - Priority 2 - Request-With-Response The value of this object is given by the sum of the above representations for those options in use on this interface. The value zero indicates that no options are in use.

dot4State.name: dot4State
dot4State.description: The current state of the 802.4 interface. The value of other(1) is used if the state is unknown (e.g., due to an error condition).

dot4Commands.name: dot4Commands
dot4Commands.description: Setting this object causes the station to change the state of the interface as indicated by the specified value. An initialize(5) command causes the interfaceto load its operational parameters from its initialization parameters; the value of dot4InitInRingDesired determines whether the station tries to enter the logical ring immediately. Note that the 802.4 specification suggests a station remain Offline after a 'remote Network Management' reset(4), until a 'local Network Management' initialize(5) is performed. Setting this object to a value of no-op(1) has no effect. When read, this object always has the value no-op(1).

dot4MacAddrLen.name: dot4MacAddrLen
dot4MacAddrLen.description: This object indicates the size of MAC addresses interpreted by this station.

dot4NextStation.name: dot4NextStation
dot4NextStation.description: The MAC address of this station's successor in the logical ring.

dot4PreviousStation.name: dot4PreviousStation
dot4PreviousStation.description: The source MAC address of the last token addressed to this station.

dot4SlotTime.name: dot4SlotTime
dot4SlotTime.description: The maximum time any station need wait for an immediate MAC-level response from another station. This value must the same in all stations on the 802.4 network.

dot4LastTokenRotTime.name: dot4LastTokenRotTime
dot4LastTokenRotTime.description: The observed token rotation time for the last token rotation, timed from token arrival to token arrival. A value of zero indicates that the token is not rotating.

dot4HiPriTokenHoldTime.name: dot4HiPriTokenHoldTime
dot4HiPriTokenHoldTime.description: The maximum duration for which a station can hold the token to transmit frames of access class 6 (if the priority option is implemented), or of any access class (if the priority option is not implemented).

dot4TargetRotTimeClass4.name: dot4TargetRotTimeClass4
dot4TargetRotTimeClass4.description: If the priority scheme is being used, this value specifies a limit on how long a station can transmit frames at access class 4. The limit is measured from the time the station is able to start transmitting frames at this access class on one rotation, to the time it must stop transmitting frames at this access class on the next rotation. If the priority scheme is not being used, this object has the value 0.

dot4TargetRotTimeClass2.name: dot4TargetRotTimeClass2
dot4TargetRotTimeClass2.description: If the priority scheme is being used, this value specifies a limit on how long a station can transmit frames at access class 2. The limit is measured from the time the station is able to start transmitting frames at this access class on one rotation, to the time it must stop transmitting frames at this access class on the next rotation. If the priority scheme is not being used, this object has the value 0.

dot4TargetRotTimeClass0.name: dot4TargetRotTimeClass0
dot4TargetRotTimeClass0.description: If the priority scheme is being used, this value specifies a limit on how long a station can transmit frames at access class 0. The limit is measured from the time the station is able to start transmitting frames at this access class on one rotation, to the time it must stop transmitting frames at this access class on the next rotation. If the priority scheme is not being used, this object has the value 0.

dot4TargetRotTimeRingMaint.name: dot4TargetRotTimeRingMaint
dot4TargetRotTimeRingMaint.description: A value used to limit the duration of a token rotation. If the duration of a token rotation exceeds this value, the station will not open the response window to solicit for a new successor.

dot4RingMaintTimerInitValue.name: dot4RingMaintTimerInitValue
dot4RingMaintTimerInitValue.description: The value to which the dot4TargetRotTimeRingMaint is set, each time the station enters the ring. A large value will cause the station to solicit successors immediately upon entry to the ring; a value of zero will cause the station to defer this solicitation for at least one token rotation.

dot4MaxInterSolicitCount.name: dot4MaxInterSolicitCount
dot4MaxInterSolicitCount.description: The maximum number of consecutive token rotations without soliciting for a successor. If this count expires, the station opens the response window to solicit for a successor (providing the duration of the current token rotation has not exceeded dot4TargetRotTimeRingMaint). The least significant two bits of the count are determined randomly by the station on a per-use basis.

dot4MaxRetries.name: dot4MaxRetries
dot4MaxRetries.description: The maximum number of retries of a Request-with-Response (RWR) frame. If the RWR option is not in use, this object has the value 0.

dot4MinPostSilencePreambLen.name: dot4MinPostSilencePreambLen
dot4MinPostSilencePreambLen.description: The minimum number of octets of preamble on the first frame transmitted by this station after a period of 'transmitted' silence.

dot4StandardRevision.name: dot4StandardRevision
dot4StandardRevision.description: The Revision number of the 802.4 standard implemented by this station.

dot4InitTable.name: dot4InitTable
dot4InitTable.description: This table contains Token Bus initialization parameters, one entry per 802.4 interface.

dot4InitEntry.name: dot4InitEntry
dot4InitEntry.description: A list of Token Bus initialization parameters for an 802.4 interface.

dot4InitIfIndex.name: dot4InitIfIndex
dot4InitIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the 802.4 interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex object, defined in [4,6], for the same interface.

dot4InitSlotTime.name: dot4InitSlotTime
dot4InitSlotTime.description: The value assigned to the object dot4SlotTime when the station is initialized.

dot4InitMaxInterSolicitCount.name: dot4InitMaxInterSolicitCount
dot4InitMaxInterSolicitCount.description: The value assigned to the object dot4MaxInterSolicitCount when the station is initialized.

dot4InitMaxRetries.name: dot4InitMaxRetries
dot4InitMaxRetries.description: The value assigned to the object dot4MaxRetries when the station is initialized.

dot4InitHiPriTokenHoldTime.name: dot4InitHiPriTokenHoldTime
dot4InitHiPriTokenHoldTime.description: The value assigned to the object dot4HiPriTokenHoldTime when the station is initialized.

dot4InitTargetRotTimeClass4.name: dot4InitTargetRotTimeClass4
dot4InitTargetRotTimeClass4.description: The value assigned to the object dot4TargetRotTimeClass4 when the station is initialized.

dot4InitTargetRotTimeClass2.name: dot4InitTargetRotTimeClass2
dot4InitTargetRotTimeClass2.description: The value assigned to the object dot4TargetRotTimeClass2 when the station is initialized.

dot4InitTargetRotTimeClass0.name: dot4InitTargetRotTimeClass0
dot4InitTargetRotTimeClass0.description: The value assigned to the object dot4TargetRotTimeClass0 when the station is initialized.

dot4InitTargetRotTimeRingMaint.name: dot4InitTargetRotTimeRingMaint
dot4InitTargetRotTimeRingMaint.description: The value assigned to the object dot4TargetRotTimeRingMaint when the station is initialized.

dot4InitRingMaintTimerInitValue.name: dot4InitRingMaintTimerInitValue
dot4InitRingMaintTimerInitValue.description: The value assigned to the object dot4RingMaintTimerInitValue when the station is initialized.

dot4InitMinPostSilencePreambLen.name: dot4InitMinPostSilencePreambLen
dot4InitMinPostSilencePreambLen.description: The value assigned to the object dot4MinPostSilencePreambLen when the station is initialized.

dot4InitInRingDesired.name: dot4InitInRingDesired
dot4InitInRingDesired.description: This object determines whether the station will attempt to enter the logical ring immediately after initialization.

dot4StatsTable.name: dot4StatsTable
dot4StatsTable.description: A table containing Token Bus statistics. All the statistics are defined using the syntax Counter as 32 bit wrap around counters. Thus, if an interface's hardware chip set maintains these statistics in 16-bit counters, then the agent must read the hardware's counters frequently enough to prevent loss of significance, in order to maintain a 32-bit counter in software.

dot4StatsEntry.name: dot4StatsEntry
dot4StatsEntry.description: An entry containing the 802.4 statistics for a particular interface.

dot4StatsIfIndex.name: dot4StatsIfIndex
dot4StatsIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the 802.4 interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex object, defined in [4,6], for the same interface.

dot4StatsTokenPasses.name: dot4StatsTokenPasses
dot4StatsTokenPasses.description: The number of times this station has passed the token.

dot4StatsTokenHeards.name: dot4StatsTokenHeards
dot4StatsTokenHeards.description: The number of tokens heard by this station.

dot4StatsNoSuccessors.name: dot4StatsNoSuccessors
dot4StatsNoSuccessors.description: The number of times the station could not find a successor while believing itself not the only station in the ring. This can signify a faulty transmitter condition in this station.

dot4StatsWhoFollows.name: dot4StatsWhoFollows
dot4StatsWhoFollows.description: The number of times the station has had to look for a new next station.

dot4StatsTokenPassFails.name: dot4StatsTokenPassFails
dot4StatsTokenPassFails.description: The number of times the station failed in passing the token to the next station.

dot4StatsNonSilences.name: dot4StatsNonSilences
dot4StatsNonSilences.description: The number of occurrences of non-silence followed by silence in which a start delimiter was not detected.

dot4StatsFcsErrors.name: dot4StatsFcsErrors
dot4StatsFcsErrors.description: The number of frames received with an incorrect FCS and the E-bit reset.

dot4StatsEbitErrors.name: dot4StatsEbitErrors
dot4StatsEbitErrors.description: The number of frames the station received with the E-bit set in the end delimiter.

dot4StatsFrameFrags.name: dot4StatsFrameFrags
dot4StatsFrameFrags.description: The number of occurrences of receiving a start delimiter followed by another start delimiter, an invalid symbol sequence or silence, without an intervening end delimiter.

dot4StatsFrameTooLongs.name: dot4StatsFrameTooLongs
dot4StatsFrameTooLongs.description: The number of frames that were received that were larger than the media's MTU.

dot4StatsOverRuns.name: dot4StatsOverRuns
dot4StatsOverRuns.description: The number of times a FIFO overrun was detected in the station.

dot4StatsDupAddresses.name: dot4StatsDupAddresses
dot4StatsDupAddresses.description: The number of times this station detected another station using the same MAC address.
